1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,771
On the one hand we have the syntax, which can be

2
00:00:02,871 --> 00:00:06,840
seen as manipulations of symbols being governed by a special theorem

3
00:00:06,940 --> 00:00:11,028
proving computer, which takes in axioms as input and outputs theorems.

4
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:14,897
Once it has proven a theorem, we can feed this

5
00:00:14,997 --> 00:00:18,198
theorem back into it's inputs to prove more theorems.

6
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:21,329
If chi is such a theorem and Sigma is out set of

7
00:00:21,429 --> 00:00:25,716
axioms then we denote this situation by this relation, which is read

8
00:00:25,816 --> 00:00:29,328
as Sigma proves chi. The theory of a given set of axioms

9
00:00:29,428 --> 00:00:32,940
is the set of all such theorems, which in our analogy is

10
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:37,198
the set of all possible outputs from our theorem proving computer.

11
00:00:37,266 --> 00:00:40,923
On the other side we have the intuitive world of semantics, where

12
00:00:41,023 --> 00:00:45,027
truth is based on Tarki's definition of truth, namely that something is

13
00:00:45,127 --> 00:00:47,801
true if and only if it is true in all models. We

14
00:00:47,901 --> 00:00:51,095
will now attempt to make this precise, which may be a bit

15
00:00:51,195 --> 00:00:53,754
boring, but it leads us to interesting places.

16
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:57,303
Formally, a structure --which we denote which this fancy

17
00:00:57,403 --> 00:00:59,812
M-- is given by this tuple of elements.

18
00:00:59,933 --> 00:01:02,244
This is some arbitrary set, and denotes

19
00:01:02,344 --> 00:01:04,718
the universe or domain of the structure.

20
00:01:04,866 --> 00:01:08,005
And these are the interpretations of the symbols of the language.

21
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:12,052
In math there are certain symbols which are known as

22
00:01:12,152 --> 00:01:16,821
the logical symbols which include variables, quantifiers, Boolean connectives --such

23
00:01:16,921 --> 00:01:21,079
as conjunction, disjunction, implication and negation-- and brackets. For a

24
00:01:21,179 --> 00:01:24,486
mathematician, these exist in the background world of logic.

25
00:01:24,533 --> 00:01:27,254
Then there are certain symbols know as the non-logical symbols

26
00:01:27,354 --> 00:01:30,212
which are the constants --like 0,1,e,pi etc., functions --such as

27
00:01:30,312 --> 00:01:33,397
addition multiplication and relations--such as <, or the set theoretic

28
00:01:33,497 --> 00:01:36,173
membership relation. These are the set of symbols specific to

29
00:01:36,273 --> 00:01:39,085
a given mathematical theory. As we saw earlier, constants simply

30
00:01:39,185 --> 00:01:41,360
get interpreted as certain elements of the domain.

31
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:45,690
The formal definition of the interpretations of function and relation symbols is a

32
00:01:45,790 --> 00:01:49,170
bit strange at first, as they get interpreted as a sets of tuples

33
00:01:49,270 --> 00:01:53,453
which satisfy a given relationship. For example, the less than relation would be

34
00:01:53,553 --> 00:01:57,415
the set of all pairs of natural numbers (a,b) such that the interpretation

35
00:01:57,515 --> 00:01:59,664
of a is less than the interpretation of b.

36
00:01:59,733 --> 00:02:03,101
We could represent this on the number line by drawing every

37
00:02:03,201 --> 00:02:06,451
possible arrow between nodes which is going to the right.

38
00:02:06,533 --> 00:02:09,079
Earlier I said that function symbols can be

39
00:02:09,179 --> 00:02:12,649
interpreted as computer programs, well, formally they will

40
00:02:12,749 --> 00:02:15,419
be interpreted as a special type of relation.

41
00:02:15,466 --> 00:02:18,965
For example the plus symbols will be interpreted as the set

42
00:02:19,065 --> 00:02:23,296
of triples (a,b,c) such that a+b=c. They are special relations, because

43
00:02:23,396 --> 00:02:27,017
we know that the output is uniquely determined by the inputs.

